---
/*
 * S01Introduction.astro — Introduction section
 *
 * Conceptual mode: void ground, copper eyebrow, Lora h1.
 * iyo-clean two-zone pattern via Section.astro's entry/content slots.
 *
 * Entry slot (min-height: 100vh, ~85% negative space):
 *   Eyebrow (conceptual/copper) → BlurReveal(h1) → lead paragraph
 *
 * Default slot (body below the entry viewport):
 *   1 paragraph → h3 sub-heading → 3 paragraphs → UpNextTeaser
 *
 * Content sourced from: .design/sections/01-introduction.md
 */
import Section from '../components/sections/Section.astro';
import Eyebrow from '../components/content/Eyebrow.astro';
import BlurReveal from '../components/content/BlurReveal.astro';
import UpNextTeaser from '../components/content/UpNextTeaser.astro';
---

<Section id="s1" label="Introduction" background="void" class="grain">

  <Fragment slot="entry">
    <div class="s01-entry">
      <Eyebrow label="INTRODUCTION" mode="conceptual" />
      <BlurReveal>
        <h1 class="s01-entry__headline">
          Amplifier is a framework for building your AI harness.
        </h1>
      </BlurReveal>
      <p class="s01-entry__lead">
        That sentence is deliberately simple, because the idea it describes is not. A harness, in the traditional sense, takes raw power and gives it direction. A climbing harness lets you use gravity safely. An electrical harness routes power to the right places. An AI harness does the same for a model: it wraps around the model and provides a controlled way to interact with the world. Some harnesses built with Amplifier are conversational AI agents: programs that can reason about a task, take actions, observe the results, and decide what to do next. Others are pipeline runners with zero AI loops. The framework does not prescribe what you build.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Fragment>

  <!-- Body content — appears below the entry viewport as reader scrolls -->
  <div class="s01-body">
    <p>
      AI models are powerful, but raw power without structure is unpredictable. The model itself handles reasoning. Everything around the model (what tools it can use, what it remembers, what rules it follows, how it talks to the outside world) needs structure. Amplifier provides that structure. Think of it as a construction kit: it gives you the pieces, and you assemble the harness that fits your use case.
    </p>

    <h3 class="s01-body__subheading">The design borrows from operating systems.</h3>

    <p>
      If you've used a computer, you've used an operating system. An operating system has a kernel at its center. The kernel is tiny relative to the whole system. It handles the most fundamental things: managing memory, scheduling tasks, letting programs talk to hardware. Everything else (the web browser, the file manager, the apps) runs on top of the kernel, plugging into it through well-defined interfaces.
    </p>

    <p>
      Amplifier borrows this structure. At the center is a small core called amplifier-core. It handles module loading, event dispatch, and session lifecycle. Which AI model to use, what tools the agent can access, how conversations are stored, what rules the agent follows: each of those is a module that plugs in from the outside.
    </p>

    <p>
      A new AI model comes out? Write a new provider module. Need the agent to follow safety rules? Add a hook module. The core does not change. It provides the infrastructure; the modules provide the behavior.
    </p>
  </div>

  <UpNextTeaser
    nextSection="Architecture Map"
    teaser="A map of the territory before we walk through it."
  />

</Section>

<style>
  /* ── Entry cluster ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   * Three elements: Eyebrow → BlurReveal(h1) → lead.
   * Eyebrow has built-in margin-bottom: var(--space-3) = 24px.
   * BlurReveal wrapper gets margin-bottom for the headline → lead gap.
   * ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .s01-entry {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  /* BlurReveal div: gap between headline and lead paragraph */
  .s01-entry :global(.blur-reveal) {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3); /* 24px: headline → lead */
  }

  .s01-entry__headline {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);        /* Lora — Voice of Ideas */
    font-size: var(--text-h1);             /* clamp(2.25rem, 4.9vw, 4.5rem) */
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: var(--leading-tight);     /* 1.15 */
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-tight); /* -0.02em */
    color: var(--text-primary);            /* #FAFAF8 bright warm-white */
    max-width: 22ch;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .s01-entry__lead {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);                      /* Inter — Voice of Structure */
    font-size: clamp(1.125rem, 1.2vw, 1.25rem);        /* --text-lead */
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);                /* 1.8 — conceptual breathing room */
    color: var(--text-body);                            /* #E8E6DC warm cream */
    opacity: 0.75;                                      /* ~60% visual weight */
    max-width: 55ch;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* em in lead — renders in warm primary, full opacity */
  .s01-entry__lead em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    opacity: 1;
  }

  /* ── Body content ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   * Paragraphs + sub-heading on the conceptual section — relaxed leading (1.8),
   * warm body text, 60ch measure for deep reading comfort.
   * ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .s01-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);           /* 24px between paragraphs */
    max-width: 60ch;
    color: var(--text-body);
  }

  .s01-body p {
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed); /* 1.8 — conceptual section */
    margin: 0;
  }

  .s01-body__subheading {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);         /* Inter — Voice of Structure */
    font-size: var(--text-h3);             /* clamp(1.125rem, 1.5vw, 1.5rem) */
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: var(--leading-tight);     /* 1.15 */
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-normal);
    color: var(--text-primary);            /* #FAFAF8 */
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
